                        <persName xml:lang="fa">محمد البلغاری</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_8619">Nuzhat al-Mulūk</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_8619">نزهة الملوک</title>
                     <note>Anecdotes collected by Muḥammad al-Bulghārī, divided into 8 bāb, each of which contains two items</note>
                     <note>The work was written in the reign of <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_43402797" role="oth" change="#role-assignment #ids-cleanup">Jahānshāh Qaraqoyunlu</persName>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For a more detailed description see Glyn Meredith-Owens: Handlist of Persian Manuscripts, 1895-1966. [London]: Trustees of the British Museum, 1968, p.89.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="Or_5327-item4" n="4" class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100075 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85046763">
                     <locus from="264r" to="288v">264r-288v ff</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_8620">Dar Faz̤īlat va Sharaf-i Insān bar Ḥayvanāt</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_8620">در فضیلات و شرف انسان بر حیونات</title>
                     <note>A controversy of an allegorical nature between men and beasts in 14 faṣls</note>
                     <note>Copied in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" notBefore="1680" notAfter="1681">1091</date>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For a more detailed description see Glyn Meredith-Owens: Handlist of Persian Manuscripts, 1895-1966. [London]: Trustees of the British Museum, 1968, p.89.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="Or_5327-item5" n="5" class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100075 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85046763">
                     <locus from="289v" to="296v">289v-296v ff</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_8621">An anecdote</title>
                     <note>An anecdote about Muḥammad Riz̤ā which describes his love affair with a beautiful girl, the daughter of a man named Ḥusayn, and his marriage to her in the face of opposition from her father, thanks to the help of the king whose name is not mentioned</note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For a more detailed description see Glyn Meredith-Owens: Handlist of Persian Manuscripts, 1895-1966. [London]: Trustees of the British Museum, 1968, p.89.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
